==================================================
1) Undoing Things
==================================================

	git commit --amend

	Forget to add file to previous commit. (Note: Old Commit gets replaced with new commit.)

	git commit -m "initial commit"

	git add forgotten_file

	git commit --amend


==================================================
2) Unstaging a staged file
==================================================
	
	git reset HEAD <File>

	Remove file from staging area i.e file that have been added (Green color)


==================================================
3) Unmodifying a Modified File
==================================================
	
	git checkout -- <file>

	Removing the changes to the file i.e file that needs to be added (Red color)